tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE user_feedback (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    feedback_text TEXT,
    comment_text TEXT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE comments (
    comment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    content_id INT,
    comment_text TEXT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE comments (
    comment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    feedback_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    comment_text TEXT,
    comment_date TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (feedback_id) REFERENCES user_feedback(feedback_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES user_feedback(user_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Comments (
    comment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    content_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    comment_text TEXT,
    commented_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE feedback (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  content_id INT,
  rating INT,
  comment TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE comments (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  content_id INT,
  comment TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
);
